    "body": "> Can you elaborate a bit about your use-case? Using abigen for this sounds a bit like shooting sparrows with cannons ..-)\r\n\r\nfirstly, I like abigen generated go code, so I can interact with contract easily, most of time I use it.\r\n\r\nsecondly, I also want to get `signed raw txn`  in the same time, so I can 1.) send raw txn to a service provider for faster broadcast 2) send a private txn to prevent front run https://docs.bloxroute.com/apis/frontrunning-protection , they only accept raw txn format.\r\n\r\nthirdly, there also have cases when people need `unsigned raw txn` format. So it can be signed by another service or private key holder, for privilege control.\r\n\r\nI can see abigen low level implementation is about to construct txn -> sign -> broadcast, how about provide a function to just return that raw txn?",
