    "body": "@huahuayu The generated code always returns the constructed transaction.\r\nYou can just set up a SimulatedBackend to deploy your transactions to, take these transactions and send them to the real backend. I don't think we should implement another mode to get raw transactions in abigen\r\ne.g.\r\n```\r\nbackend,_ := ethclient.Dial(\"infura\")\r\nfakeBackend,_ := getSimBackend()\r\n_, tx, _, err := DeployIO(txopts, fakeBackend) // deploy on fake backend\r\nbackend.SendTransaction(context.Background(), tx)\r\n```",
